iSign Solutions Inc. Key Developments

iSign Solutions Inc. Announces Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
May 16 17
iSign Solutions Inc. announced earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported total revenue of $211,000, a decrease of $65,000, or 24%, compared to total revenue of $276,000 for the prior year. For the quarter ended March 31, 2017, the net loss attributable to common stockholders was $614,000, a decrease of $1,817,000, or 75%, compared to a net loss attributable to common stockholders of $2,431,000 in the prior year. This decrease primarily was due to a $575,000 decrease in loss from operations, resulting from the above-mentioned decrease in operating expenses offset by the decrease in revenue, a $245,000 decrease in accretion of beneficial conversion feature, an $854,000 decrease in preferred stock dividend expense, a $90,000 decrease in interest expense and an $82,000 decrease in amortization of debt discount.


iSign Solutions Inc. Appoints Mike Engmann as President & Coo, Effective May 15, 2017
May 11 17
iSign Solutions Inc. announced that its Board of Directors has appointed Michael Engmann to serve as President and Chief Operating Officer of iSIGN, effective as of May 15, 2017. Mr. Engmann currently is co-chairman of iSIGN's Board of Directors and is a long-term shareholder of the company.


iSign Solutions Inc. Reports Earnings Results for the Year Ended December 31, 2016
Mar 31 17
iSign Solutions Inc. reported earnings results for the year ended December 31, 2016. For the period, the company's total revenue of $1,065,000 for the year ended December 31, 2016, a decrease of $555,000, or 34%, compared to total revenue of $1,620,000 for the prior year. Net loss attributable to common stockholders was $5,057,000, a decrease of $2,562,000, or 34%, compared to a net loss attributable to common stockholders of $7,619,000 in the prior year. This decrease primarily was due to a $616,000 decrease in loss from operations from 2015 to 2016, resulting from decrease in operating expenses offset by the decrease in revenue, a $312,000 increase in gain on derivative liability, a $281,000 decrease in accretion of beneficial conversion feature and a $1,863,000 decrease in preferred stock dividend expense, offset by a $164,000 increase in interest expense and a $337,000 increase in amortization of debt discount.


